Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) with identical electrodes have gained interesting attention because of their simplified fabrication procedure and reduced processing costs.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, their development is limited by their electrocatalytic activity and stability of the electrode materials used.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, we report a prototypical SrFeO3-d-based perovskite oxide with formula GdxSr1-xFeO3-d (GSF) as a highly effective SSOFC electrode material.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that A-site Gd substitution in SrFeO3-d greatly improved its structural stability under reducing atmosphere.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, doping Gd was able to significantly enhance the electrochemical activity, achieving area-specific resistances of 0.18 U cm2 for the cathode and 0.003 U cm2 for the anode at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lower polarization resistance could be attributed to the abundant surface oxygen species through the Gd-doping in SrFeO3-d. Benefiting from superior electrochemical activity and structural stability, the symmetrical cell with GSF-0.2 electrode showed reasonable stability and electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results show that the developed GSF perovskite oxide may be a promising candidate as electrode material for symmetrical SOFCs.
Titulo: Gadolinium-doped SrFeO3 as a highly active and stable electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
